= Project ORC

21 October 2008

This is a preview alpha of the XXX CMS which is an awesome Ruby on Rails Content Management System.
This has been written as part of the Final Project of Nate Walker for RocketBoys Ltd.


== Maintainer Contact
Nate Walker (Nickname: kiwinewt)
< kiwinewt (at) gmail (dot) com >

== Requirements
This CMS requires:
* Ruby on Rails >= 2.1
* The ferret gem
Depending on your setup:
* The mysql gem
* The sqlite3-ruby gem
  
To automatically install the *required* gems, run:
* rake gems:install

== Documentation
To generate documentation, run the command:
  rake doc:app
For more information, visit:
  http://doc.rocketboys.co.nz/xxxcms

== Installation Instructions
1. Extract all the folders and files to the root of your web directory. You should then have this directory structure:
   * app
   * config
   * db
   * doc
   * lib
   * LICENCE
   * log
   * public
   * Rakefile
   * README
   * script
   * vendor
2. Please read the LICENCE file
3. Configure the CMS for your preferences by copying these files to these locations then modifying them as required:
   * config/config.yml.sample                config/config.yml
   * config/database.yml.sample              config/database.yml
   * config/ferret_server.yml.sample         config/ferret_server.yml
   * config/initializers/mail.rb.sample      config/initializers/mail.rb
4. Uncomment the first line in config/environment.rb:
   * # ENV['RAILS_ENV'] ||= 'production'
5. Create the database by running rake db:create then rake db:migrate from the command line
6. Run the CMS from whatever Rails server setup you use. On a development machine, Mongrel is a good starting server.

* Please raise issues, bugs, contributions in the forum - see http://www.rocketboys.co.nz/xxxcms

== Usage Overview
1. Open a web browser and access the site from whatever location the server is set to run from
   * (e.g.: http://localhost:3000)

2. Login with the following settings:
   * user: admin
   * password: admin
  
3. Create new pages and blogs via the menus.

4. For new themes, please visit:
   * http://www.rocketboys.co.nz/pages/xxxcms-themes
  
5. For information on how to create a custom theme, please visit:
   * http://doc.rocketboys.co.nz/xxxcms-themes

== Known issues
* Modified Plugins:
  * app_config
    * modified to allow the application variables to be changed while it is running, without having to restart the application
    * Currently in the process of being tested and uploaded to GitHub.
